description: SAMI MOKBEL: Bayern have agreed a £100million deal for Kane but have been left waiting to complete the historic transfer amid concern at the German club that the deal was stalling.

title: Callie Mitchell dies a week after being found unconscious from heart condition at cheer camp in Texas
description: A Texas family is in mourning after their 16-year-old daughter died unexpectedly after being found unconscious while away cheerleading camp in July.

title: New York State Psychiatric Institute has ALL human research trials suspended by watchdog after person taking part in Parkinson's drug trial kills themselves
description: The New York State Psychiatric Institute has suspended all human research trials after a person taking part in a Parkinson's drug trial killed themselves.

title: Everyone hated the outfit I wore to my friend's wedding and said it was inappropriate - but I loved it (even if it broke the dress code)
description: A young woman has been labelled an 'attention seeking brat' after wearing a 'tasteless' outfit on her friend's wedding day.

title: TOM UTLEY: The day my toddler vanished bottom-first into a first century wine jar at Pompeii... and other unforgettable Utley family holiday calamities
description: TOM UTLEY: Nobody wants to hear about balmy evenings spent sipping rosé by the pool. But a holiday from hell, now, that's quite a different matter.

title: Olivia Pratt-Korbel's mother accuses the government of 'dragging their heels' on laws which would force killers to appear for their sentencing
description: Killer Thomas Cashman, 34, killed nine-year-old Olivia Pratt-Korbel (pictured) at her home in Dovecot, Liverpool, last year, and then refused to show up to his 42-year jail term in April.

title: Teenage cyclist is killed in hit-and-run: Police arrest man in his 50s over death of boy after crash between truck and pedal bike
description: Police were called to Swafield, Norfolk, at 6.24pm after reports of that a white Ford Ranger truck struck a bike.

title: BRIAN VINER: It's little wonder that Sky has decided to ditch its Oscars broadcast... who would want to sit through this pompous woke-fest anyway?
description: BRIAN VINER Only once have I sat through the entire Academy Awards ceremony from start to finish.

title: Drivers see the average price of car insurance shoot up by £88 in a year to the highest levels since 2012
description: The average premium paid for private comprehensive insurance in the second quarter of 2023 was £511 - up 7 per cent on the previous quarter.

title: Dangerous carbon monoxide alarms from China are sold online amid concern not enough is being done to protect the public
description: Consumer champion Which? said it found 149 listings for unsafe CO alarms across four online marketplaces - which had all subsequently been removed.

title: Sky to stop broadcasting the Oscars after 20 years as viewing figures for the awards ceremony tumble
description: According to a report the network has backed away from keeping the rights to the event as viewing figures tumble.

title: Retailers renew their plea to the Government to scrap the UK's tourist tax after China lifts its Covid-era ban on group tours of Britain
description: Before the pandemic, Chinese tourists spent more than any other country when abroad - clocking up around £200 billion in 2019, around 60 per cent of which came from groups.

title: Owners of Britain's 'wonkiest pub' that burned down in 'arson attack' are now accused of tearing down 20ft-tall trees, ripping up orchids and destroying wildlife in 'mini personal New Forest' after gutting ANOTHER popular village boozer
description: Adam Taylor and his wife Carly owned the Crooked House in Himley, Staffordshire when a major blaze broke out over the weekend - just days after the 18th-century inn was sold to them.

title: Nicola Sturgeon says she wants the police probe into the SNP finances 'to be over' as the former First Minister says the investigation and her subsequent arrest has been 'difficult' and 'traumatic'
description: The former First Minister opened up about the 'traumatic experience' of being at the centre of a major investigation.

title: The UK trains 1,000 Ukrainian marines to conduct daring amphibious assaults on Russian-occupied territory
description: The troops will be flown back to Ukraine in the coming days after being taught by Britain's elite Royal Marines and Army Commandos.

title: Alabama boat brawl: Woman, 21, is the fourth person charged after handing herself in for assaulting a black riverboat crew co-captain - as she appears puffy-eyed in her mugshot
description: Mary Todd, 21, turned herself in, according to Major Saba Coleman of the Montgomery Police Department. She is the fourth person charged with assaulting a black riverboat crew co-captain.

title: 999 operator listened on the phone as gang who broke into cannabis factory run by rivals stabbed 25-year-old Albanian man to death, court hears
description: Five men are on trial at Lewes Crown Court after 25-year-old Xhovan Pepaj, was stabbed 16 times in a property in Caley Road, Tunbridge Wells, Kent, in the early hours of 4 December 2021

title: AI could be used to detect major complications of diabetes by scanning a patient's eyes
description: Researchers from the University of Liverpool and Manchester Metropolitan University are tweaking equipment currently used by high street optometrists to detect diabetic peripheral neuropathy.

title: Lunar Drive-in cinema in Dandenong, Melbourne officially closes with tradies seen tearing down movie screen
description: Onlookers captured footage of the moment an excavator tore down the large cinema screen at the Lunar Drive-in, located in Melbourne's southeast, this week.

title: Controlling boyfriend who flushed his partner's rabbit down the toilet is still on the run in Thailand: Fugitive thug, 23, is jailed in his absence after campaign of abuse which saw him shoot victim with a BB gun and goad her into taking an overdose
description: Fugitive Nicholas Cash, 23, (pictured) from Bournemouth, Dorset, controlled and coerced Olivia Croft, 21, during their nine-month relationship.

title: Mike Pence gets asked why he's a TRAITOR at the Iowa State Fair : Ex-VP insists he was 'always loyal' to 'friend' Trump until January 6 - as he pushes ex-president to take the debate stage
description: Mike Pence's debut at the Iowa State Fair Thursday turned dramatic when an audience member asked him why he was a traitor for not helping former President Donald Trump overturn the 2020 election.

title: Ron DeSantis shrugs off attacks from Trump, Joe and Kamala, saying it means they see him as a THREAT as he, Casey and the kids barnstorm Iowa to try and raise his sinking poll numbers
description: Ron DeSantis shrugged off attacks he's receiving from Donald Trump, Joe Biden and Kamala Harris, saying it just means they see him as a 'threat.'  He, Casey and the kids are campaigning across Iowa.

title: Alistair McGowan says doing impressions could be a dying art because younger audiences don't watch television and won't get it
description: Comedian Alistair McGowan, 58, (pictured) lamented that in the 21st century, his 'methodology doesn't really work for a modern audience'.

title: Hawaii wildfires could destroy the state's tourism-reliant economy just as it was recovering from pandemic - as a pilot films dramatic video of wildfires razing Lahaina to the ground
description: Lahiana officials have ordered tourists to stay away from the wildfire-devastated area as they assess the damage, sparking fears over the crisis' effect on Hawaii's tourism-reliant economy.

title: Ministers continue to back 'renewable' energy companies such as Drax despite accusations it 'gamed' subsidy rules to avoid repaying hundreds of millions of pounds to taxpayers
description: Drax, which runs a power plant near Selby, North Yorkshire, continues to reel from claims it manipulated the green subsidies regime during the energy crisis triggered by the Russian invasion of Ukraine

title: Tony Abbott launches scathing attack on the Indigenous Voice to Parliament: 'We are a country with no privilege of origin'
description: Former Prime Minister Tony Abbott (pictured) gave a speech at an Institute of Public Affairs event in Perth on Wednesday night where he reasoned why he'd be voting no.
